main event: On 3rd February 1956 in Glenwood, Iowa, a civilian reported sighting two round, dime-sized, stacked silver balls in the sky moving south for 3 minutes, with an aircraft in the vicinity. The duty controller initially believed the objects to be aircraft.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, dime-sized, and stacked silver balls, indicating a unique and unusual appearance.
There were no photographs available to accompany the report, suggesting a lack of visual evidence for the sighting.
The duty controller believed the objects were likely aircraft, indicating the initial skepticism towards identifying them as UFOs.
The sighting lasted 3 minutes, offering a substantial duration for observation and analysis.
The objects were seen moving south, suggesting a specific direction of travel.
sighted object: Two round, dime-sized, stacked silver balls in the sky
